        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>April 20<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Prof. Victor Carus wishes to translate into German my volume on “Volcanic Islands” &amp; that on “S. America”. He says that he cannot procure a copy; but I remember you telling me about a year ago, that you had plenty of copies.— Will you be so kind as to inform me whether you have a copy of each so that I may inform Herr. Koch, the publisher.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Begging that you will excuse my troubling you I remain | Dear Sir | Yours very faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10453.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. V. Carus, 16 April 1876</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10453.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from J. V. Carus, 16 April 1876</ref>. <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8001.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Volcanic islands</hi></ref> and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7343.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">South America</hi></ref>, parts of CD’s geological observations on the <hi rend="italic">Beagle</hi> voyage, were published by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4407.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Smith, Elder &amp; Co</ref>. in 1844 and 1846 respectively. <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2732.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Eduard Koch</ref> was head of CD’s German publisher, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4246.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">E. Schweizerbart’sche Verlagsbuchhandlung</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
